Design a thread-safe solution around the state machine from goal 01, identifying exactly which data structures need to be wrapped with their own mutex (via the project's `threadsafe` facility) and mapping each piece of their internal state to the states and transitions described in `RPC-mode.md`. The design must show how the locking strategy prevents every race catalogued during the investigation (the follow-up-vs-active-run window, the mutating-command-after-success window, and any others), without relying on careful call-site ordering.
